00:30:58,234 --> 00:31:02,798
for Google and worry about having it be front page news if I even hinted something like

487
00:31:02,818 --> 00:31:03,018
that.

488
00:31:03,238 --> 00:31:07,001
I see some of my fellow Googlers are smiling ruefully at that one.

489
00:31:08,562 --> 00:31:12,923
So the trick is, and I only covered this one area here,

490
00:31:13,363 --> 00:31:16,764
but if you learn about the ways that the eye and the brain interact,

491
00:31:17,204 --> 00:31:21,166
you can actually get little cues, little clues really,

492
00:31:21,526 --> 00:31:24,507
that you can use to then ferret out these systems

493
00:31:24,547 --> 00:31:28,088
and find ways that you can take shortcuts that can make the VR quality better.

494
00:31:28,388 --> 00:31:30,868
So that's all I'm going to say about the motion side.

495
00:31:32,100 --> 00:31:35,722
But motion is an important part of the sense of immersion

496
00:31:35,882 --> 00:31:36,842
that we get in VR.

497
00:31:37,202 --> 00:31:39,384
That word, immersion, gives you this sense

498
00:31:39,644 --> 00:31:41,245
of this nice warm bath.

499
00:31:41,645 --> 00:31:43,946
And certainly, VR is pretty amazing

500
00:31:44,907 --> 00:31:48,008
when it gets everything right of how

501
00:31:48,068 --> 00:31:49,689
you feel that you're actually in the moment.

502
00:31:49,849 --> 00:31:50,550
It's just.

503
00:31:52,551 --> 00:31:57,096
It's almost indescribable and the nice thing is this is one of the few areas where everyone

504
00:31:57,136 --> 00:31:59,359
has had that experience and knows what it's like.

