00:39:02,206 --> 00:39:04,689
saying, hey, we can scare people with this stuff.

626
00:39:05,089 --> 00:39:08,692
And it turns out that VR is really good at scaring people.

627
00:39:09,493 --> 00:39:14,516
I don't know if you've seen maybe first hand or maybe the videos of people who were put

628
00:39:14,556 --> 00:39:19,420
into some kind of horror game and took their thousand dollar headset and threw it against

629
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:24,643
the wall before they realized, oh gee, sorry I was just so scared I had to get it off my

630
00:39:24,663 --> 00:39:25,904
head as quickly as possible.

631
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:28,245
So probably not a great thing to do.

632
00:39:31,328 --> 00:39:35,210
Cinema, as with some of these other things I've mentioned, has been experimenting with these things.

633
00:39:35,230 --> 00:39:36,950
They're great as a place to learn from.

634
00:39:37,851 --> 00:39:42,752
My friend Hal Barwood, who is a film director and writer before he got into the games industry,

635
00:39:43,092 --> 00:39:47,514
had all sorts of interesting stories like this, including one about 3D sound

636
00:39:47,554 --> 00:39:49,895
and how when they started to first do surround sound,

637
00:39:50,455 --> 00:39:55,416
they found that people were about three times as likely to jump from the exact same sound

638
00:39:55,476 --> 00:39:57,297
played behind them as in front of them.

639
00:39:57,937 --> 00:40:02,319
Again, from an evolutionary standpoint, it makes perfect sense why we are hardwired to

640
00:40:02,339 --> 00:40:06,240
be a lot more scared of stuff that's creeping up behind us than stuff that we can see in

641
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:07,601
front of us.

642
00:40:07,681 --> 00:40:13,203
With the 3D stuff, of course, all the way up even to frustratingly movies that are coming

643
00:40:13,323 --> 00:40:19,365
out this very week, there's stuff being thrown at your face to kind of, oh no.

644
00:40:19,405 --> 00:40:24,787
That may work the very first time you've seen it, but please don't keep doing that.

645
00:40:25,027 --> 00:40:26,808
It gets very thin very quickly.

646
00:40:27,962 --> 00:40:33,265
you end up with something that will look as dated as our little monster here does very

