00:40:58,545 --> 00:41:02,750
when this girl sort of pops out in 3D, even just looking at the screen,

655
00:41:02,790 --> 00:41:04,071
it's a little bit disturbing.

656
00:41:04,752 --> 00:41:09,477
But why is it so disturbing? Why is horror in VR so strong?

657
00:41:11,607 --> 00:41:14,728
This is one of those areas where there's some very clear brain science behind it.

658
00:41:15,288 --> 00:41:19,209
At the very bottom center of this, there's the amygdala called out.

659
00:41:19,630 --> 00:41:22,250
And the amygdala is a very old part of the brain.

660
00:41:22,290 --> 00:41:24,871
It's present in fish and reptile brains.

661
00:41:24,931 --> 00:41:28,352
In fact, it's much larger in proportion to the entire brain.

662
00:41:28,872 --> 00:41:32,195
in a lot of our ancestors and our relatives like that.

663
00:41:33,116 --> 00:41:38,561
Our cerebral cortex, all that big gray matter where you do a lot of your critical thinking,

664
00:41:38,861 --> 00:41:41,784
is a relatively recent addition compared to the amygdala.

665
00:41:42,244 --> 00:41:46,188
And what the amygdala can handle are some very basic functions.

666
00:41:46,849 --> 00:41:50,150
Fear is one of the primary things among them.

667
00:41:50,510 --> 00:41:52,611
It also handles anger and aggression.

668
00:41:52,671 --> 00:41:56,053
And those two together give you the famous fight or flight

669
00:41:56,233 --> 00:41:58,754
that you need when you're under a threat

670
00:41:59,134 --> 00:42:01,575
to be able to decide almost instantly,

671
00:42:01,875 --> 00:42:03,296
should I run away from this thing?

672
00:42:03,336 --> 00:42:04,076
Should I fight it?

673
00:42:04,656 --> 00:42:07,137
And that is so much built into our DNA.

674
00:42:08,699 --> 00:42:14,963
that it's the first thing that comes up before we do any kind of extra processing on that.

675
00:42:15,023 --> 00:42:20,307
One of the things that the amygdala also controls that is also just as deep and just as important

676
00:42:20,427 --> 00:42:26,311
for propagation and evolution is arousal and intimacy.

677
00:42:26,351 --> 00:42:32,396
This is also part of our brain that gets activated in romance and when somebody is close to us

678
00:42:32,456 --> 00:42:33,937
physically or emotionally.

679
00:42:35,246 --> 00:42:38,910
A lot of that is mediated by the amygdala.

680
00:42:39,711 --> 00:42:45,998
Now in video games, the fight or flight stuff, aggression, fear, we're really good at that

681
00:42:46,058 --> 00:42:46,618
sort of thing.

